body:
Jaime walked toward her, bending on one knee with his sword presented to her, his eyes cast down.

“I offer my services, Lady Stark. I will shield your back and keep your counsel and give my life for yours if need be. I swear it by the Old Gods and the New”

He lifted his green eyes and they met her icey blue ones. He breathed out a hesitant

“….if you’ll have me”

It was only a moment but it felt like an eternity for Jaime. He thought to say something again, maybe even turn and run, until Sansa nodded and then stood.

"And I vow that you shall always have a place by my hearth, and meat and mead at my table. And I pledge to ask no service of you that might bring you dishonor. I swear it by the Old Gods and the New. Arise, Ser Jaime”

He did not leave her side from that day forward.

body:
april 28th — song birds

characters: sansa stark, margaery tyrell

relationship: sansa stark/margaery tyrell

warnings: n/a

notes: an au takes place sometime in season 3.

The waves crashed against the rocks and Margaery wondered why the birds sang to this. It reminded her of Westeros- violence always piqued the interest of peasants, a chirping crowd of avians who flocked over at the sight of blood.

She liked calling everyone her birds. They were such feeble, delicate creatures. So beautiful, yet so fragile. Margaery was to be their queen, their ruler. The bird of all birds.

“What are you looking at?”

She turned at the voice of her friend. Sansa stood in front of her with a long dress, hair wrapped in a simple Highgarden fashion that made the Tyrell smile in memory of her home. “The water, the birds. It’s very beautiful up here.”

“I suppose King’s Landing can be pretty from certain spots.” The red-haired woman took a few steps closer to look over the edge.

“The entire place is pretty if you look hard enough.” She linked her arms with Sansa’s. “You haven’t seen the smallfolk enough, have you?”

The Stark shivered at the thought. “I’ve had my experiences.”

“Bad ones, I can tell.”

Sansa looked up. “I don’t know how they like you so much.”

“Are you jealous?”

“No!” Smiles played on both of their faces. “Of course not!” Sansa trailed off, her eyes moving down to look at the water distantly. A few birds chirped above them, while another dove into the water to catch a fish. It came out with nothing.

“The smallfolk aren’t much different from you and I.” Margaery took her arm out of Sansa’s and grabbed her hands. “Put them in a castle or put a sword in their hands and they’d be the same as one of us.”

“Or they’d kill us all.” Sansa turned away and moved towards one of the stone benches that lined the rock wall. “I’ve encountered them before in riots. I was attacked, and if it weren’t for the Hound I’d have-“

“A small few are like that.” Lies, it’s far more. “I’ve met many kind ones. Besides, we highborns kill each other all the time.”

Sansa laughed at that, and Margaery tipped her head to the side with a smile. A few birds flew down to the rock wall, chirping and hopping. “Song birds,” Sansa spoke in fascination. “We didn’t see many birds in Winterfell. Besides ravens and crows.”

Margaery held her hand out, watching the bird with hopeful eyes. It hopped close to her, chirped a little sound, and flew away. The other followed quickly, taking no look back at them.

“Highgarden has many,” she mused. “Far too many. They always eat the plants and try picking berries off the trees.”

“Pesky little birds.” Sansa smiled.

The waves crashed against the rocks, but Margaery didn’t see. She heard. Everything around her had a sound: the water, the birds, the expressions on Sansa’s face. The song birds continued to sing their songs above, while Sansa and Margaery sang their songs below.

—————————

An artist I follow on Instagram is doing a GoT Tarot series (link attached) and just release Sansa as the “Strength” card and I am LIVING for it…I love the callback to the classic Rider-Waite “Strength” card showing a person taming a lion…

this is the card Sansa deserves!!! She is one of the strongest characters of this story (if not THE strongest imo) and she is constantly mis-characterized as “weak” or “useless” because her main character trait isn’t killing people or being good at killing people.

"A crown for our cute little Queen"
"Here, princess, a gift from us."
And Theon and Robb put something on her head. 
"It's a...
body:
“A crown for our cute little Queen”

“Here, princess, a gift from us.”

And Theon and Robb put something on her head.

“It’s a crown !” Theon said proudly.

“We added flowers to make it look prettier.” Robb said.

The crown was only made of twigs and a few daisies but little Sansa thought it was the most beautiful of all Westeros.

○○○○

Some cute headcanon and childhood memory before an episode that will surely break our hearts.

summary:
Me: *Sees Jaime knighting Brienne*
Me: Alright, I don’t care who dies next episode, as long as these can live long happy lives...
body:
Me: *Sees Jaime knighting Brienne*

Me: Alright, I don’t care who dies next episode, as long as these can live long happy lives together.

Me: *Sees Theon and Sansa reunite, while also taking comfort in each other*

Me: … okay, I don’t care who does so long as these FOUR…

Me: *Sees Grey Worm and Missandei being soft and making plans for the future*

Me: *sweating* OKAY, I don’t care who does as long as…

Me: *Seea Arya and Gendry finally do the do after being separated from each other for SIX FUCKING SEASONS*

Me: *heavy breathing*

Me: *thinks about all the character I love and have grown up watching*

Me: So can I just not watch the episode tonight?

Me 2 ½ hours from now:
